== English ==
=== Verb form ===
'''depreciated'''
# Simple past and past participle of [[depreciate]]; reduced in value over time.
#* '''2006:''' ''The World Factbook'' -- The [[currency]] '''depreciated''' sharply in 2001 and 2002, which contributed to a dramatic [[current account adjustment]]; in 2003 to 2005, [[Brazil]] ran record trade surpluses and recorded its first [[current account surplus]]es since 1992. [http://www.odci.gov/cia/publications/factbook/geos/br.html]

==== Usage note ====
This verb form is often used mistakingly for [[deprecated]].
* '''2001:''' ''Java&tm; 2 SDK, Standard Edition Documentation, Version 1.3.1'' -- "[[Deprecated]]" and "'''depreciated'''" are not same. "'''Depreciated'''" is a [[financial]] term that means "[[lowered]] [[value]]". Although the meanings are similar, [[class]]es and [[method]]s are [[deprecated]], not '''depreciated'''. [http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.3/docs/guide/misc/deprecation/deprecation.html]